<h2>Upcoming brainlife.io events</h2>

<h3>Making Open Neuroscience Infrastructures Interoperable 3.0</h3>
<p>
March 18 | Montreal
</p>

<p>
As neuroinformatics infrastructures become increasingly important in research with big and open neuroscience data, this conference will discuss how to make these infrastructures interoperable. At 3 p.m., brainlife‚Äôs Franco Pestilli will present ‚ÄúConnecting major open data projects with computational resources using Brainlife.io.‚Äù 
</p>

<a href="https://www.mcgill.ca/neuro/channels/event/making-open-neuroscience-infrastructures-interoperable-30-303671">Event info</a>

<h3>2020 Organization for Human Brain Mapping</h3>
<p>
June 26-30 | Montreal
</p>

<p>
Come find the brainlife.io team at OHBM! We will have a booth at the conference entrance where you can chat with our team about the platform. There will also be a brainlife.io software demonstration at the conference. More info to come!
</p>

<a href="https://www.humanbrainmapping.org/i4a/pages/index.cfm?pageid=3947">Event info</a>
        
<hr>

<h2>Featured jobs & learning opportunities</h2>

<h3>Apply now: Student developers working in deep learning at brainlife.io</h3>
<p>
Do you want to work with the brainlife.io team this summer? We are hiring undergraduates or graduate students who are interested in developing apps on brainlife.io as part of an internship or fellowship. You must have experience in neuroimaging research. You can work on-campus in Franco Pestilli's lab or remotely. 
</p>

<a href="mailto:franpest@indiana.edu">Contact Franco for more details</a>

<h3>Apply now: Statistics/Neuroimaging postdoc positions in Department of Statistics at Indiana University
</h3>
<p>
<a href="https://mandymejia.com/">Dr. Mandy Meija</a> is accepting applications on a rolling basis for postdocs with computational neuroimaging backgrounds. Fellows will work in a cross-disciplinary team with researchers at Johns Hopkins University, the Kennedy Krieger Institute, CUNY, and the University of Utah. 
</p>

<a href="https://mandymejia.com/945-2/">Apply now</a>

<h3>DIPY Workshop</h3>  
<p>
March 16-20 | Indiana University Bloomington 
</p>

<p>
Run through <a href="https://dipy.org/">DIPY</a> tutorials at the novice, intermediate, or advanced level and analyze your own data with more than 15 DIPY developers who will be on-site to help you.
</p>

<p>        
Deadline to Register is March 10.
</p>

<a href="https://workshop.dipy.org/#Home">Event info</a>

<h3>Midwest Undergraduate Cognitive Science Conference (MUCSC)</h3>
<p>
April 4 | Indiana University Bloomington</p>
<p>

<p>
This conference is an opportunity for undergraduates to practice their research presentation skills through poster sessions and live talks related to cognitive science.
</p>
        
<p>        
Submit your abstract by March 6.
</p>

<a href="http://mucsc.info/#submit">Event info</a>      
                                        
